pageContext.claim: “Then we won Utah. Remember we were supposed to lose Utah? We won... We only won by 22 points, you know.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump was never expected to be in danger of losing Utah. He won Utah by less than 18 percentage points, and only received 45 percent of the vote in the state because Hillary Clinton and independent Evan McMullin received 27.2 and 23.1 percent, respectively.
